  Dialogue:
  - "The third pillar\u2026"
  - <color=purple>William</color> already imagined that that bard would argue against
    the arrest and say something about freedom of speech.
  - Be quiet, nothing you say can prevent you from being arrested.
  - "<color=red>Kuvira</color>'s third pillar\u2026 freedom of speech."
  - <color=purple>William</color> thought how predictable that bard was, he didn't
    even understand that he was being arrested for raising his daggers against a
    warrior and not for the music he played.
  - You bards are too cowardly to commit crimes into your own hands, but your music
    constantly encourages people to break the law. <color=red>Kuvira</color> always
    made it very clear that apology for crime would never be allowed.
  - We are free only to agree with the <color=yellow>law</color>.
  - That bard began to laugh.
  - Why are you laughing? You lost.
  - I lost a fight, but I won where it matters. I won in being happier, because while
    you decided to be a slave to the <color=yellow>law</color>, I decided to be a
    slave to my passions. Even if I die now, I will be satisfied that I lived my
    life to the fullest.
  - Are you happier than me?
  - <color=purple>William</color> reduced that bard's happiness.
  - And now?
  - I'm sorry.
  - <color=purple>William</color> reduced that bard's happiness.
  - Please! Stop... please.
  - Are you even happier than I am?
  - Please! Stop... please.
  - No... no!
  - That bard started having trouble breathing.
  - "You're more\u2026happy\u2026than I am."
  - <color=purple>William</color>'s <color=red>happiness</color> increased.
  DialogueBR:
  - "O terceiro pilar\u2026"
  - "<color=purple>William</color> j\xE1 imaginava que aquele bardo argumentaria
    contra a pris\xE3o e diria algo sobre liberdade de express\xE3o."
  - "Fique quieto, nada do que voc\xEA disser pode impedir que voc\xEA seja preso."
  - "Terceiro pilar de <color=red>Kuvira</color>\u2026 a liberdade de express\xE3o."
  - "<color=purple>William</color> pensou como aquele bardo era previs\xEDvel, ele
    nem entendia que estava sendo preso por levantar suas adagas contra um guerreiro
    e n\xE3o pela m\xFAsica que tocava."
  - "Voc\xEAs bardos s\xE3o muito covardes para cometerem crimes com suas pr\xF3prias
    m\xE3os, mas suas m\xFAsicas constantemente encorajam as pessoas a infringirem
    a lei. <color=red>Kuvira</color> sempre deixou bem claro que a apologia ao crime
    nunca seria permitida."
  - Somos livres apenas para concordarmos com a <color=yellow>lei</color>.
  - "Aquele bardo come\xE7ou a rir."
  - "Por que voc\xEA est\xE1 rindo? Voc\xEA perdeu."
  - "Eu perdi a luta, mas ganhei onde importa. Ganhei em ser mais feliz, porque enquanto
    voc\xEA decidiu ser escravo da <color=yellow>lei</color>, eu decidi ser escravo
    das minhas paix\xF5es. Mesmo que eu morra agora, estarei satisfeito por ter vivido
    minha vida ao m\xE1ximo."
  - "Voc\xEA \xE9 mais feliz do que eu?"
  - <color=purple>William</color> reduziu a felicidade daquele bardo.
  - E agora?
  - Me desculpe.
  - <color=purple>William</color> reduziu a felicidade daquele bardo.
  - Por favor! Pare... por favor.
  - "Voc\xEA ainda \xE9 mais feliz do que eu?"
  - Por favor! Pare... por favor.
  - "N\xE3o... n\xE3o!"
  - "Aquele bardo come\xE7ou a ter dificuldade para respirar."
  - "Voc\xEA \xE9 mais... feliz... do que eu."
  - A <color=red>felicidade</color> de <color=red>William</color> aumentou.
  DialogueES:
  - 'El tercer pilar...

'
